Sentencas: Ta5+ and Mo6+ substituted SrFeO3-delta perovskites were researched as cathodes of intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Cobalt-free perovskite SrTa0.1Mo0.1Fe0.8O3-δ as cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The samples were synthesized with three components, e.g. mono-doped SrTa0.2Fe0.8O3-delta, SrMo0.2Fe0.8O3-delta and co-doped SrTa0.1Mo0.1Fe0.8O3-delta.
Titulo: Cobalt-free perovskite SrTa0.1Mo0.1Fe0.8O3-δ as cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Their phase structure, thermal stability, electrical conductivity and electrochemical catalytic property were researched comparatively.
Titulo: Cobalt-free perovskite SrTa0.1Mo0.1Fe0.8O3-δ as cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Ta5+ and Mo6+ co-doped SrTa0.1Mo0.1Fe0.8O3-delta possesses better electrochemical catalytic activity than that of the mono-doped SrFeO3-delta.
Titulo: Cobalt-free perovskite SrTa0.1Mo0.1Fe0.8O3-δ as cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The performance difference between the mono-doped and co-doped SrFeO3-delta has a close relation with the different contents of oxygen vacancy in the materials.
Titulo: Cobalt-free perovskite SrTa0.1Mo0.1Fe0.8O3-δ as cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The synergistic effect derived from Ta5+ and Mo6+ co-doping enhances the amount of oxygen vacancies in material, thus resulting in its better electrochemical property.
Titulo: Cobalt-free perovskite SrTa0.1Mo0.1Fe0.8O3-δ as cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The cells with SrTa0.1Mo0.1Fe0.8O3-delta as cathode deliver a R-p of 0.085 omega center dot cm(2) and an output of 931 mW center dot cm(-2) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Cobalt-free perovskite SrTa0.1Mo0.1Fe0.8O3-δ as cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
